# ---- Define IHF equation from TSC temperature (calibrations performed in January 2018)
def c_disc(x):
    """
    Calculates the correction factor as a function of the disc's temperature
    """
    return -5.5282e-4*x + 0.5520

        df[column_name] = np.append(np.diff(df.iloc[:,i+1]),0)/np.append(np.diff(df['Elapsed_time']*60),1)

In [13]:
# ---- constants used in IHF equation
ALPHA_disc = 0.8 # absorptivity (-)
MASS_disc = 4.6566*10**(-6) # kg
AREA_disc = 7.854*10**(-7) # m2
GAMMA_factor = 0.7 # (-)
EPSILON_disc = 0.75 # (-) emissivity
STEFAN_BOLTZ = 5.670367*10**(-8) # Wm^2K^4
CONVEC_COEFF = 10 # assumed constant Wm^-2K-1
In [15]:
# ---- See excel file on TSC calibrations folder from January_2018
def heat_cap(x):
    """
    Calculates the heat capacity of the disc as a function of temperature
    """
    return (x+273.15)*0.2125 + 382.32

# ---- Juan's paper on TSCs. Returns IHF in Wm^-2
def incident_hf(T,dT,amb_T):
    """
    Calcualtes the IHF from an energy balance on the disc
    """
    return (1/(ALPHA_disc*(1-c_disc(T))))*((GAMMA_factor*(MASS_disc/AREA_disc)*heat_cap(T)*dT) + \
                                           (EPSILON_disc * STEFAN_BOLTZ*(T+273.15)**4) + CONVEC_COEFF*(T-amb_T))
# ---- ambient temperature for each test
ambient_temperature = [17,16,15] 

# ---- Calculate IHF per TSC
for j,df in enumerate(all_experiments):
    for i in range(8):
        col_name_IHF = 'IHF_' + str(i + 1)
        df[col_name_IHF] = incident_hf(df.iloc[:,i+1],df.iloc[:,i+9],ambient_temperature[j])

for k,df in enumerate(all_experiments):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2,sharey = "row", figsize = (25,12))
    fig.tight_layout()
    distance = [2,4]
    test = ["alpha_2", "beta_2", "gamma"]

    for i in range(2):
        if i == 0:
            ax[i].plot(df.loc[:, "Elapsed_time"], df.iloc[:,17:21]/1000)
            ax[0].set_ylabel('IHF $[kW/M^2]$', fontsize = FS_label)
        if i == 1:
            ax[i].plot(df.loc[:, "Elapsed_time"], df.iloc[:,21:25]/1000)
        ax[i].set_title(f"IHF - {test[k]}. Distance = {distance[i]} meters", fontsize = FS_graph)
        ax[i].set_xlabel('Time [min]', fontsize = FS_label)
        ax[i].set_ylim([0,50])
        ax[i].set_xlim([0,100])

# ---- Smoothing the IHF curves using a lowess algorithm
from statsmodels.nonparametric.smoothers_lowess import lowess

for i,df in enumerate(all_experiments):
    for i in range(8):
        column_name = f"sIHF_{i}"
        df[column_name] = lowess(df.iloc[:,i+17],df.loc[:,'Elapsed_time'], frac = 0.05, it=0, return_sorted = False)

# ---- Plotting MIX/MAX IHF and internal temperatures in the compartment
fig,ax = plt.subplots(3,1, sharex = True, sharey = True)

for i,df in enumerate(all_experiments):  
    # ---- Flashover
    line1 = ax[i].plot([flashover_times[i], flashover_times[i]],[0,1200], lw = line_plot_width - 1, linestyle = "--", color = "k", alpha = alpha_lines)
    
    # ---- Temperature
    line2 = ax[i].plot(all_temp[i].loc[:,"Time [min]"], all_temp[i].loc[:,"Tav"], lw = line_plot_width, color = "crimson") 
    ax[i].set_ylim([0,1200])
    ax[i].set_yticks(np.linspace(0,1200,5))
    
    # ---- IHF
    ax2 = ax[i].twinx()
    ax2.fill_between(df.loc[:,"Elapsed_time"], df.iloc[:,25:29].max(axis = 1)/1000, df.iloc[:,25:29].min(axis = 1)/1000, alpha = alpha_shaded_areas, color = "teal", label = "IHF")
    ax2.set_xlim([0,60])
    ax2.set_ylim([0,40])
    ax2.set_yticks(np.linspace(0,40,5))
    
    if i == 1:
        ax[i].set_ylabel("Temperature [$^\circ C$]")
        # Quick solution to get the ax.fill_between on the legend
        ax2.set_ylabel("IHF [$kW/m^2$]")
        proxy = ax2.fill(np.NaN, np.NaN, color = "teal", alpha=alpha_shaded_areas)
        ax2.legend([line2[0], proxy[0],line1[0]], ["Average Radiating Hot Layer Temperature", "IHF","Flashover"],loc = "lower right",frameon = True, fancybox = True)
        
    
    
ax[2].set_xlabel("Time [$min$]")

plt.savefig("IHF_temperatures.png", bbox_inches = "tight")
plt.savefig("IHF_temperatures.eps", format = 'eps', bbox_inches = 'tight')

del proxy, line1, line2
